{{Infobox person |image = Anastasia Zampounidis.jpg |image_size = 200px |name = Anastasia Zampounidis |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1968|12|28|mf=y}} |birth_place = [[Thessaloniki]], [[Greece]] |occupation = [[VJ (media personality)|VJ]] on [[MTV]] [[Germany]], [[Actor]] }} '''Anastasia Zampounidis''' ({{lang-el|Αναστασία Ζαμπουνίδη}}; born December 28, 1968), is a [[Greeks|Greek]]-[[Germany|German]] [[television presenter|TV host]].
==Climb to fame== After graduating from high school, Zampounidis spent time in [[Los Angeles]] as an [[au pair]], [[Go-Go dancing|Go-Go dancer]], and language tutor. While in LA she broadcast a radio program for [[Berlin]] radio. She ranked #55 2001, #68 2002, #57 2003 and #98 2004 in [[FHM]]-[[Germany]]'s Sexiest Women.
