{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox person | name = Roger De Courcey | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1944|12|10}} | birth_place = London, England | death_date = | death_place = | other_names = | occupation = British [[ventriloquist]], actor, writer | known_for = | spouse = Cheryl McCandless (1 Child) | website = }}
'''Roger De Courcey''' (born 10 December 1944 in London, England) is a British [[ventriloquist]], best known for performing with '''Nookie Bear'''. He was the winner of the 1976 ''[[New Faces]]'' televised talent competition grand final.
==Biography== De Courcey has performed on the West End stage, in productions of musicals ''[[Sweet Charity]]'', ''Two Cities'' and ''[[Company (musical)|Company]]''. He has appeared at the [[London Palladium]] many times including the 1976 [[Royal Variety Performance]] in the presence of [[Queen Elizabeth the Queen Mother]].
A [[Freemasonry|freemason]], he is a member of Chelsea Lodge No. 3098, the membership of which is made up of entertainers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chelsea-lodge.org.uk/|title=Chelsea Lodge No.3098|publisher=Chelsea-lodge.org.uk|accessdate=26 December 2014}}</ref> De Courcey is also a member and former "King Rat" of the [[Grand Order of Water Rats]] which is the oldest theatrical fraternity in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rogerdecourcey.co.uk|title=Biography|website=Roger De Courcey|accessdate=11 October 2017}}</ref> De Courcey is also an agent, and represents musician [[Rick Wakeman]], and broadcaster [[David "Kid" Jensen]].
On 27 December 2009, it was revealed that Roger and Nookie Bear had been formally invited to take part in the ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 7]]'' in January 2010.
De Courcey is also a fan of Crystal Palace Football Club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.holmesdale.net/page.php?id=82&story=4154&p=3|title=Celebrity Palace fans|work=Holmesdale Online|accessdate=26 December 2014}}</ref>
==References== {{Reflist}}
