A '''tamborita''' is a type of [[Bolivia]]n ensemble which plays folk music. A typical group contains a [[Tamborita calentana|tamborita]] (a type of [[bass drum]]), a [[Caja vallenata|caja]] ([[snare drum]]), a [[flute]] (which could be made of diverse materials), [[maracas]] and [[cymbals]].
Its repertory covers brincaos, chobenas, carnavales, [[Polka#Styles|polcas]], [[cueca]]s, [[cumbia]]s, and canciones (songs) from Bolivia, Mexico and other South American countries.
